Common.SpaceDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE has been retained as the exclusive advisor for the sale of 2823 West Fulton Street, Chicago, IL near the bustling Fulton Market neighborhood, which is rapidly expanding west into the Kinzie Industrial Corridor. The offering presents qualified investors with the opportunity to acquire a unique centrally located asset with stable income in place and the opportunity to capture Chicago’s growing appetite for redevelopment projects as dated industrial areas in are transformed into modern offices, retail, and multi-family hot spots.

This prime long-term hold opportunity is less than one mile from bustling Fulton Market neighborhood and Kinzie Industrial Corridor. There is an extremely limited supply of adaptive reuse and future redevelopment opportunities within the neighborhood comparable to scale, style, and size of 2823 W. Fulton.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Flexible 2.36-acre site with ample expansion, parking, and/or storage space
Cohesive plan for single-use and multi-tenant users
Immediate access to transportation, including I-290 via Sacramento Ave. and walking distance to California Ave./Lake St. Green Line CTA Station
Exposed brick and timber, metal barrel truss, and lofted ceilings with skylights appeal to the aesthetics and demand of creative, makers, and innovator tenants
Over 24k SF of surface lot area, which provides ample car parking or outside storage capabilities as demand within neighborhood rapidly increases
Planned CTA Green Line Station at Damen Ave. and Lake St. spurring economic growth in the surrounding area
